title: GREAT DANE VELO CLUB Spring Crits
MWCCC Conference Championsips Hosted by Wisconsin Cycling
description:
A team time trial and a criterium will be held April 22nd in Madison, WI

The road race will be held the following morning 35 minutes west of Madison in the Town of Vermont.
course:
will be located in the UW-Madison Arboretum.  Parking will be available in the Arboretum Visitor’s Center parking lot.  Participating teams and clubs will be encouraged to enter through the west entrance of Arboretum Drive, off Seminole Hwy, to reduce traffic congestion in the area where the race will take place.

The race will begin at the visitor’s center and follow Arboretum Drive northeast where a U-turn will be completed just before reaching the intersection with S. Mills St.  The road surface is in excellent condition, because it was paved early in 2016. 

The Criterium will also be held Saturday the 22nd.  The course itself will be on the UW-Madison campus and 0.7 miles with no change in elevation.  Parking will be available to those who wish to stay the duration of the event may park in Lot 62, which will be surrounded by the lap, but there are other parking options in the immediate vicinity that will not be affected by the lap

The road race will be held on Sunday the 23rd, and is based at Brigham County Park in the Town of Vermont, just outside of Blue Mounds, WI.  The Park will serve as the start finish,  from where riders will roll out to the 11.2-mile loop, which runs clockwise. Each race will finish with a 4.0 mile, 750-foot climb back up County Road F. to Brigham County Park for the finish.  Plenty of parking will be available on the park grounds. 

The Men's C race will leave at 9:00AM, for 3 loops, next the Men's D race at 9:05AM and Women's B/C at 9:10, both will complete 2 loops. At 11:40AM the Men's A race will depart for 6 loops, followed by the Men's B's and Women's A, at 11:45AM and 11:50AM, respectively, each totaling 4 loops each. The last race will finish at approximately 3:30PM.
registration: Registration will be held online through the USA Cycling website and there will be on site registration available for those unable to use the site
notes:
Road Race Course Directions

Brigham County Park: Follow CTH F for 6.7 miles
Right on Pleasant Valley Rd. for 1.4 miles
Left on Blue Mounds Tr. For 2.0 miles
Right on CTH JJ for 4.1 miles
Continue straight on CTH J for 0.7 miles
Continue straight on CTH F for next loop
OR Left on CTH F for 4 miles to the Finish
directions:
The events that take place on Saturday will occur within downtown Madison.  The road race can be reached by taking:
TTT: Longenecker Drive, Madison, WI 53713
Criterium: 2024 Observatory Drive, Madison, WI 53706
Road Race: Park Road, Blue Mounds, WI 53517

Additional Road Race Directions:
Nakoma Rd
L on Midvale which turns into Verona Rd
Verona Rd. then becomes HWY 151
After Mt. Horeb take a right on Cave of the Mounds Rd
followed by a R on HWY F
Brigham County Park will be on the right

title: JDRF Ride to Cure - La Crosse
John Hatherly Mid Century Ride - Waupaca
description:
This ride for charity offers quiet and scenic roads in Waupaca, WI.  Through very generous sponsors, this ride has raised nearly $200,000 in the past 6 years which all has gone to high school seniors at Waupaca H.S. in the form of college scholarships.

Various distances for all types of riders are available.  It is not an overly crowded ride which allows for plenty of room on the roads.
course:
There are multiple distances that will all begin and end at Waupaca High School.  Because of the flower-petal design of the course, you can build your own distance based on how you feel that day.  Standard distances include 12, 20, 50, 62, 70 and 100 miles.  The 100 mile course will be two loops of the 50 mile distance.
 
There will be a two rest stop locations.  The first will be at high school.  Riders will pass this rest stop at mile mile 20 and again at mile 50.  In addition, there will be a rest stop at mile 32.  100 mile riders will also see this rest stop at mile 82.

title: Trek Cx Cup Cross Clinic
description:
Trek Pro Cyclocross Clinic
Join Sven Nys, Ellen van Loy, and more of pro cyclocross’ biggest names for an hour of private instruction on the skills and insider training and competition tips that have made them the sport’s brightest stars. This exclusive clinic is open only to 30 people with all proceeds benefiting DreamBIkes. 
This clinic is open to the public but requires registration to reserve a spot. 

What: Your chance to learn from the world’s best cyclocross racers in an exclusive experience limited to just 30 people
Who: Sven Nys, Ellen van Loy, and other Trek athletes will be on hand to teach YOU the tips and tricks that have helped them win some of the world’s biggest cyclocross races
When: Friday, September 22 – 10:00am – 1 hour
Where: Meet at the start line of the course for World Cup Waterloo at Trek’s Global HQ – 801 W. Madison St. Waterloo, WI 53594
Why: 100% of proceeds from this exclusive event will benefit DreamBikes
How: Be one of the first 30 people to give us $50 at trekcxcup.com
course: Clinic is held on the same course as World Cup Waterloo
notes: Bring your bike, your shoes and helmet and get ready for some fun
directions: Trek’s Global HQ – 801 W. Madison St. Waterloo, WI 53594
